data.name: label41.Text
data.value: Excel uses a tabbed Ribbon system instead of traditional menus. The Ribbon contains multiple tabs, each with several groups of commands. You will usethese tabs to perform the most common tasks in Excel.

data.name: label39.Text
data.value: The Ribbon and Quick Access Toolbar are where you will find the commands to perform common tasks in Excel. The Backstage view gives you various options for saving, opening a file, printing, and sharing your document.

data.name: label26.Text
data.value: Some parts of the Excel window (like the Ribbon and scroll bars) are standard in most other Microsoft programs. However, there are other features that are more specific to spreadsheets, such as the formula bar, name box, and worksheet tabs.

data.name: label33.Text
data.value: Excel is a spreadsheet program that allows you to store, organize, and analyze information. While you may think Excel is only used by certain people to processcomplicated data, anyone can learn how to take advantage of the program's powerful features. Whether you're keeping a budget, organizing a training log, or creating an invoice, Excel makes it easy to work with different types of data.
